{"parentUuid":"56edecad-9060-4eda-9956-d74763a2be55","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"1bf10c99-62f4-4218-b383-52b74f3e3d8c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to create a COMSOL simulation prompt (提示词) for their ultrasonic Fresnel zone plate project. They've provided a reference example of a COMSOL prompt for a joule heating simulation, and they want me to craft a similar prompt tailored to their project.\n\nLet me think about what their project needs from a COMSOL simulation perspective:\n\n1. The project is about ultrasonic Fresnel zone plate focusing effect\n2. They need to simulate acoustic wave propagation through the zone plate\n3. Key physics: Pressure Acoustics in frequency domain (40 kHz)\n4. The zone plate has alternating open/blocked rings (Soret type)\n5. Key parameters: f=40kHz, λ=8.5mm, F=120mm, N=10 rings\n6. They want to visualize the acoustic pressure field behind the zone plate\n\nLet me design a comprehensive COMSOL prompt. I should think about:\n\n- The geometry: a cylindrical/spherical domain with the zone plate\n- Physics: Pressure Acoustics, Frequency Domain\n- The zone plate can be modeled as either:\n  a) Actual geometry with alternating rings\n  b) Boundary conditions (sound hard boundary on blocked rings, radiation on open rings)\n- Post-processing: extract focal point, pressure distribution, gain\n\nLet me think about the best approach for COMSOL:\n\nOption A: Full 3D model with actual zone plate geometry - very heavy computationally\nOption B: 2D axisymmetric model - much more efficient, and the zone plate is rotationally symmetric\n\nFor 40 kHz ultrasound (λ=8.5mm), the zone plate diameter is about 220mm. A full 3D model would need a very large mesh. 2D axisymmetric would be much more practical.\n\nLet me create a detailed prompt for the COMSOL simulation.\n\nActually, the user said their teammate has successfully connected Claude Code to COMSOL via MCP. They need a prompt that they can give to Claude Code to drive COMSOL to simulate their project. The reference prompt is for a joule heating model, and they want a similar style prompt but for their ultrasonic Fresnel zone plate project.\n\nLet me craft this carefully:\n\n1. The prompt should be in Chinese (matching the reference style)\n2. It should follow the same structured step-by-step format\n3. It should cover the specific physics of their project\n4. It should include error handling guidance\n\nLet me think about the COMSOL setup:\n\n**Geometry options:**\n- 2D axisymmetric is the most practical (the zone plate is circular)\n- The domain: a rectangle representing r-z plane\n- Zone plate rings as boundaries on the bottom or interior\n\nActually, let me think more carefully. The Fresnel zone plate has alternating open and blocked rings. In COMSOL, we can model this as:\n- A plane wave incident from one side\n- The zone plate is a thin barrier with alternating sound-hard (blocked) and sound-transparent (open) regions\n- The open regions let the wave pass through\n- This can be modeled in 2D axisymmetric\n\n**Physics setup:**\n- Pressure Acoustics, Frequency Domain\n- Incident plane wave from the left/top\n- The zone plate rings are modeled as interior boundaries or as a boundary condition\n- PML (Perfectly Matched Layer) on the outer boundaries to absorb outgoing waves\n\nLet me write the prompt now. I'll write it to a plan file since we're in plan mode.\n\nWait, the user said \"我需要你给我一份关于我们这个项目仿真的提示词\" - they want a prompt they can give to Claude Code that will control COMSOL via MCP. This is a deliverable, not something to implement in their VSCode workspace. Let me write this as a plan.\n\nActually, re-reading the instructions: \"Plan mode is active. The user indicated that they do not want you to execute yet -- you MUST NOT make any edits (with the exception of the plan file mentioned below)\"\n\nSo I should write the plan file, then call ExitPlanMode. Let me create a comprehensive plan that includes the COMSOL prompt.\n\nLet me also think about what the user might need beyond just the COMSOL prompt. They said \"我希望你能帮我规划一下我们要先完成哪些工作，给我一份实验仿真方案\" - they want both a work plan AND a simulation plan. Since I already provided the work plan in my previous response (before plan mode was activated), now I should focus on the simulation plan/prompt.\n\nLet me write the COMSOL prompt as the main deliverable, and include it in the plan file.\n\nFor the COMSOL simulation, let me think about the most practical approach:\n\n**Approach: 2D Axisymmetric Pressure Acoustics**\n\nDomain (r-z plane):\n- r: 0 to ~150 mm (radius)\n- z: -50 to ~200 mm (axial direction, with zone plate at z=0)\n\nSetup:\n1. Background pressure field (plane wave) incident from z < 0\n2. Zone plate rings at z=0 plane:\n   - Odd rings (m=1,3,5,7,9): open → sound soft boundary (p=0) or radiation condition\n   - Even rings (m=2,4,6,8,10): blocked → sound hard boundary (∂p/∂n=0)\n3. PML on outer boundaries to absorb scattered waves\n4. Frequency domain at 40 kHz\n\nBut wait, for the Soret type zone plate, odd rings are OPEN and even rings are BLOCKED. In COMSOL:\n- Open rings: the wave passes through unimpeded. We can model this as the incident wave field being \"on\" in these regions, or more practically, as the zone plate surface having alternating boundary conditions.\n- Blocked rings: sound hard boundary (wall condition, ∂p/∂n=0)\n\nActually, the simplest approach might be to model the zone plate as an interior boundary with an impedance condition that varies radially:\n- For blocked rings: very high impedance (sound hard)\n- For open rings: matched impedance (transparent)\n\nOr even simpler: use a background field and model the zone plate as a piston source with alternating active/inactive rings.\n\nLet me think about this differently. In the experiment:\n- There's an ultrasonic transducer emitting 40 kHz\n- The wave passes through the zone plate\n- The zone plate blocks every other ring (even rings for Soret type)\n- The open rings act as secondary sources that interfere constructively at the focal point\n\nIn COMSOL, I think the cleanest approach is:\n\n1. Use \"Pressure Acoustics, Frequency Domain\" in 2D axisymmetric\n2. Set up a background pressure field (plane wave traveling in +z direction)\n3. Place the zone plate as a boundary at z=0 with a spatially-varying condition:\n   - For r in blocked ring regions: Sound Hard Boundary (Wall)\n   - For r in open ring regions: no condition (wave passes through)\n4. Use PML at the far boundaries\n5. Solve and extract the pressure field\n\nNow let me write the actual prompt. I need to be specific about dimensions, ring radii calculations, etc.\n\nLet me pre-calculate the ring radii:\n- λ = 340/40000 = 0.0085 m = 8.5 mm\n- F = 120 mm\n- ρ_m = √(mλ/2 · (2F + mλ/2))\n- ρ_1 = √(1×0.0085/2 × (2×0.12 + 1×0.0085/2)) = √(0.00425 × (0.24 + 0.00425)) = √(0.00425 × 0.24425) = √0.001038 = 0.03222 m = 32.22 mm\n- ρ_2 = √(2×0.0085/2 × (2×0.12 + 2×0.0085/2)) = √(0.0085 × (0.24 + 0.0085)) = √(0.0085 × 0.2485) = √0.002112 = 0.04596 m = 45.96 mm\n- ρ_3 = √(3×0.00425 × (0.24 + 3×0.00425)) = √(0.01275 × (0.24 + 0.01275)) = √(0.01275 × 0.25275) = √0.003222 = 0.05677 m = 56.77 mm\n- ρ_4 = √(4×0.00425 × (0.24 + 0.017)) = √(0.017 × 0.257) = √0.004369 = 0.06610 m = 66.10 mm\n- ρ_5 = √(5×0.00425 × (0.24 + 0.02125)) = √(0.02125 × 0.26125) = √0.005551 = 0.07451 m = 74.51 mm\n- ρ_6 = √(6×0.00425 × (0.24 + 0.0255)) = √(0.0255 × 0.2655) = √0.006770 = 0.08228 m = 82.28 mm\n- ρ_7 = √(7×0.00425 × (0.24 + 0.02975)) = √(0.02975 × 0.26975) = √0.008024 = 0.08958 m = 89.58 mm\n- ρ_8 = √(8×0.00425 × (0.24 + 0.034)) = √(0.034 × 0.274) = √0.009316 = 0.09652 m = 96.52 mm\n- ρ_9 = √(9×0.00425 × (0.24 + 0.03825)) = √(0.03825 × 0.27825) = √0.010643 = 0.10316 m = 103.16 mm\n- ρ_10 = √(10×0.00425 × (0.24 + 0.0425)) = √(0.0425 × 0.2825) = √0.012006 = 0.10957 m = 109.57 mm\n\nOK, so the ring radii match the document's claim of ρ_10 = 109.57 mm.\n\nFor Soret type: odd rings (1,3,5,7,9) are OPEN, even rings (2,4,6,8,10) are BLOCKED.\n\nIn COMSOL 2D axisymmetric:\n- r=0 is the axis of symmetry\n- We need to create a rectangular domain representing the r-z plane\n- At z=0, we place the zone plate with alternating boundary conditions\n\nLet me now write the prompt. I should use the plan file for this.\n\nActually, wait. The user is in plan mode. They want me to produce a plan. The plan should contain the COMSOL prompt. Let me write this to the plan file.\n\nBut actually, the user's main request is for \"一份关于我们这个项目仿真的提示词\" - a prompt for their teammate to use with Claude Code + COMSOL. This is more of a deliverable than a plan. But since we're in plan mode, let me write it as a plan file and then exit plan mode.\n\nLet me draft the COMSOL prompt now. I should write it in Chinese, matching the style of the reference prompt they provided.\n\nLet me also think about whether to use 2D axisymmetric or full 3D. \n\n2D axisymmetric advantages:\n- Much faster computation\n- The zone plate is rotationally symmetric, so this is a perfect match\n- Mesh size is dramatically smaller\n\n3D advantages:\n- Can show full 3D visualization (but 2D axisymmetric can be revolved)\n- Can handle non-axisymmetric effects (but there shouldn't be any in this ideal case)\n\nI'll go with 2D axisymmetric - it's the right choice for this problem.\n\nNow, for the zone plate representation in COMSOL, I need to think about how to model \"open\" vs \"blocked\" rings:\n\nThe cleanest approach in 2D axisymmetric:\n1. The zone plate is a line at z=0 (or a very thin domain)\n2. Blocked rings → Sound Hard Boundary (Wall) condition: ∂p/∂n = 0 (zero normal acceleration)\n3. Open rings → no special condition (the wave passes through as if nothing is there)\n\nBut wait, in COMSOL, how do we represent a plane wave passing through some regions and being blocked by others?\n\nI think the best approach is:\n- Set up the domain as the entire r-z plane\n- Use \"Background Pressure Field\" to define an incident plane wave\n- The zone plate is modeled as an interior boundary at z=0\n- On this boundary, apply \"Sound Hard Boundary\" on the blocked ring regions\n- The open ring regions have no condition (continuity of pressure and normal velocity)\n\nThe background pressure field in COMSOL can be set up as a plane wave: p_b = p0 * exp(-i*k*z)\n\nThen we solve for the scattered field. The total field = background + scattered.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. In COMSOL's Pressure Acoustics module, we can:\n1. Add a \"Background Pressure Field\" feature\n2. Define it as a plane wave\n3. The zone plate acts as a scatterer\n\nThis is the standard approach for scattering problems in COMSOL.\n\nLet me now write the full prompt. I'll include:\n1. Model setup (2D axisymmetric)\n2. Parameters definition\n3. Geometry creation\n4. Physics setup (Pressure Acoustics)\n5. Mesh\n6. Study\n7. Post-processing\n\nLet me write this to the plan file now. The plan file should contain both:\n- The work plan (brief, since I already described it)\n- The detailed COMSOL simulation prompt (main deliverable)\n\nNow let me calculate if 2D axisymmetric is valid. The axis of symmetry should be at r=0. The zone plate is centered at r=0. The rings are concentric around r=0. Yes, this is perfectly axisymmetric.\n\nOne issue: the incident wave. In reality, the transducer is a finite disk source, not an infinite plane wave. For a first simulation, plane wave approximation is fine (the transducer is at a distance >> wavelength from the zone plate). But we might want to mention this as a simplification.\n\nOK let me write the full prompt now. I want to make sure it's:\n1. Detailed enough that Claude Code + MCP can execute it step by step\n2. Includes fallback guidance when things go wrong\n3. Has clear parameter calculations\n4. Covers all aspects from geometry to post-processing\n\nLet me also consider: should the zone plate be modeled as a boundary condition or as actual geometry?\n\nBoundary condition approach (simpler):\n- The zone plate is a line at z=0\n- Alternating sections have sound hard boundary\n- Advantage: simple geometry, clean physics\n\nGeometry approach (more realistic):\n- Create thin annular rings as actual domains\n- Assign different materials (air for open, sound-hard material for blocked)\n- Advantage: more realistic, can account for plate thickness\n\nI'll go with the boundary condition approach for simplicity, and mention the geometry approach as an alternative.\n\nActually, for MCP-based COMSOL control, the boundary condition approach is much more reliable since it avoids complex geometry operations. Let me use that.\n\nNow let me write the actual prompt:\n\n---\n\nLet me also think about what else to include. The user's teammate needs:\n1. Step-by-step instructions that the MCP can follow\n2. Checkpoints to verify each step\n3. Error handling guidance\n4. Post-processing to extract focal spot data\n\nLet me now write this to the plan file.","signature":"1bf10c99-62f4-4218-b383-52b74f3e3d8c"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1904,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":38016,"output_tokens":7833,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"2df42398-fc51-4edc-86f2-c50676bb0a38","timestamp":"2026-05-29T08:36:49.521Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"d:\\豆包\\vscode文件","sessionId":"2563aa1c-2760-4099-ae80-555560773076","version":"2.1.145","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"claude-code-comsol-comsol-multiphysics-groovy-otter"}
{"parentUuid":"2df42398-fc51-4edc-86f2-c50676bb0a38","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"1bf10c99-62f4-4218-b383-52b74f3e3d8c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"text","text":"好的，你的需求很明确——需要一份能让 Claude Code 通过 MCP 驱动 COMSOL 完成超声菲涅尔波带片声场仿真的提示词。让我把这个作为正式计划写下来。"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1904,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":38016,"output_tokens":7833,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"3b3069d7-5f66-4dba-8446-fb4b605d7dd1","timestamp":"2026-05-29T08:36:50.594Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"d:\\豆包\\vscode文件","sessionId":"2563aa1c-2760-4099-ae80-555560773076","version":"2.1.145","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"claude-code-comsol-comsol-multiphysics-groovy-otter"}
{"parentUuid":"3b3069d7-5f66-4dba-8446-fb4b605d7dd1","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"1bf10c99-62f4-4218-b383-52b74f3e3d8c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_00_w6f7BZQXSB8cG4WsMjvo0689","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Nijika\\.claude\\plans\\claude-code-comsol-comsol-multiphysics-groovy-otter.md","content":"# 超声菲涅尔波带片 COMSOL 仿真方案\n\n## Context\n物理创新竞赛项目\"超声菲涅尔波带片聚焦效应的可视化测量系统\"需要在硬件搭建前进行 COMSOL 声场仿真，验证焦距 F=120mm、聚焦增益、焦斑尺寸等关键指标。队友已成功接入 Claude Code + COMSOL MCP，需要一份可直接使用的详细提示词。\n\n---\n\n## 一、COMSOL 仿真提示词（可直接使用）\n\n以下是给 Claude Code + COMSOL MCP 的完整提示词，按步骤执行即可：\n\n---\n\n```\n你现在是一位专业的 COMSOL Multiphysics 声学仿真工程师。请通过 MCP 接口，完全自动地帮我从零搭建并求解一个\"空气中 40 kHz 超声波通过菲涅尔波带片（Soret 型）的聚焦效应\"仿真模型。\n\n本仿真的物理背景：\n- 40 kHz 超声波（波长 λ = 8.5 mm）以平面波形式入射到菲涅尔波带片上\n- 波带片为 Soret 型（奇数环开放、偶数环遮挡），环数 N=10，设计焦距 F=120 mm\n- 需要计算波带片后方的声压分布，验证聚焦效应，提取焦点坐标和焦斑尺寸\n\n为了确保每一步成功，请你在执行过程中仔细检查 MCP 的返回结果。如果遇到几何 ID 或边界 ID 不确定的情况，请利用坐标查询（bounding box 或坐标过滤）来获取正确的 Domain/Boundary ID，不要盲目瞎猜。\n\n请按以下严格的步骤执行：\n\n---\n\n### 第一步：参数定义与环带半径计算\n\n在 COMSOL 的 Global Definitions > Parameters 中定义以下参数：\n\n| 参数名 | 表达式 | 单位 | 说明 |\n|--------|--------|------|------|\n| f0 | 40[kHz] | Hz | 超声频率 |\n| c_air | 340[m/s] | m/s | 空气中声速 |\n| lam | c_air/f0 | m | 波长 (≈8.5 mm) |\n| F_design | 120[mm] | m | 设计焦距 |\n| N_rings | 10 | - | 总环数 |\n| p0 | 1[Pa] | Pa | 入射声压幅值（参考值） |\n| R_domain | 150[mm] | m | 仿真域半径 |\n| Z_up | 150[mm] | m | 波带片上游域长度 |\n| Z_down | 200[mm] | m | 波带片下游域长度 |\n\n然后计算并记录 10 个环带的外半径（作为后续几何建模的依据）：\n\n**环带外半径公式：** ρ_m = sqrt( m * lam/2 * (2*F_design + m*lam/2) )\n\n请用 Global Definitions 中的 Analytic 函数或直接计算以下值并确认（单位 mm）：\n- ρ_1 = 32.22, ρ_2 = 45.96, ρ_3 = 56.77, ρ_4 = 66.10, ρ_5 = 74.51\n- ρ_6 = 82.28, ρ_7 = 89.58, ρ_8 = 96.52, ρ_9 = 103.16, ρ_10 = 109.57\n\n对于 **Soret 型波带片**：奇数环（m=1,3,5,7,9）开放，偶数环（m=2,4,6,8,10）遮挡。\n\n---\n\n### 第二步：创建几何（2D Axisymmetric）\n\n**重要：使用二维轴对称 (2D Axisymmetric) 建模**，r=0 为对称轴，z 为轴向。\n\n1. 将空间维度设为 **2D Axisymmetric**。几何单位设置为 **mm**。\n\n2. 创建仿真域（空气域）—— 一个大矩形：\n   - 创建 Rectangle：宽度 = R_domain (150 mm)，高度 = Z_up + Z_down (350 mm)\n   - 位置：r=0, z=-Z_up (-150 mm)\n   - 此矩形代表 r-z 平面上的空气域\n   - 标签命名为 \"Air Domain\"\n\n3. 创建波带片（作为内部边界，用线段表示）：\n   - 波带片位于 z=0 处，从 r=0 延伸到 r=ρ_10 (109.57 mm)\n   - 创建 Line Segment / Polyline：起点 (r=0, z=0)，终点 (r=ρ_10, z=0)\n   - 注意：这不是一个面，而是一条线，将作为内部边界施加声学条件\n   - 替代方案：如果 MCP 不支持直接创建内部边界线，可以创建一个极薄的矩形（厚度 0.5 mm）代表波带片实体，然后用材料属性区分开放和遮挡环带\n\n4. 如果 MCP 支持，在波带片线上按环带半径创建分割点（Split Points），将线段分成 11 段：\n   - 分割点位置：r = 0, ρ_1, ρ_2, ρ_3, ..., ρ_10\n   - 这样后续可以为每段分别设置边界条件\n\n5. 创建 PML（完美匹配层）吸收域：\n   - 在空气域的右边界 (r = R_domain)、上边界 (z = Z_down)、下边界 (z = -Z_up) 各创建一个厚度 20 mm 的 PML 层\n   - PML 用于吸收出射波，消除边界反射\n\n6. 执行\"构建所有 (Build All)\"，完成几何创建。\n\n7. **务必查明并记录**：\n   - 空气域对应的 Domain ID\n   - 波带片边界（z=0 的线段）的 Boundary ID 及其各分段的 ID\n   - 对称轴 (r=0) 的 Boundary ID\n   - 上、下、右外侧 PML 边界的 Boundary ID\n\n---\n\n### 第三步：添加材料\n\n1. 为空气域添加 \"Air\" 材料：\n   - 从 COMSOL 内置材料库 (Built-in) 中添加 \"Air\"\n   - 分配给整个空气域 (All Domains)\n   - 确认空气的声速为 340 m/s，密度为 1.2 kg/m³（可在 Materials 中查看）\n\n---\n\n### 第四步：配置物理场（Pressure Acoustics, Frequency Domain）\n\n添加物理场：**压力声学，频域 (Pressure Acoustics, Frequency Domain, acpr)**。\n\n#### 4.1 基础设置\n- 作用于所有域（空气域 + PML 域）\n- 频率设置为 f0 (40 kHz)\n\n#### 4.2 背景压力场（入射平面波）\n- 添加 \"Background Pressure Field\" 节点\n- 类型选择：**Plane wave (平面波)**\n- 传播方向：+z 方向（即从波带片下方垂直入射）\n- 压力幅值：p0 (1 Pa)\n- 相位：0\n- 此设置表示一列平面波从 z < 0 方向射来，穿过波带片向 +z 传播\n\n#### 4.3 波带片边界条件（关键步骤！）\n\n在 z=0 的线段上，按环带设置不同的边界条件：\n\n**对于开放环带（奇数环 m=1,3,5,7,9）：**\n- 不添加额外边界条件\n- 或添加 \"Continuity\" 条件（压力和法向速度连续）\n- 这些区域声波自由通过\n\n**对于遮挡环带（偶数环 m=2,4,6,8,10）：**\n- 添加 **Sound Hard Boundary (Wall)** 条件\n- 含义：法向加速度 = 0，声波被完全反射\n- 物理上代表这些环带被固体材料遮挡\n\n具体环带区间（r 范围）：\n- 环 1 (开放): r = 0 ~ 32.22 mm\n- 环 2 (遮挡): r = 32.22 ~ 45.96 mm → 加 Wall\n- 环 3 (开放): r = 45.96 ~ 56.77 mm\n- 环 4 (遮挡): r = 56.77 ~ 66.10 mm → 加 Wall\n- 环 5 (开放): r = 66.10 ~ 74.51 mm\n- 环 6 (遮挡): r = 74.51 ~ 82.28 mm → 加 Wall\n- 环 7 (开放): r = 82.28 ~ 89.58 mm\n- 环 8 (遮挡): r = 89.58 ~ 96.52 mm → 加 Wall\n- 环 9 (开放): r = 96.52 ~ 103.16 mm\n- 环 10 (遮挡): r = 103.16 ~ 109.57 mm → 加 Wall\n\n> **如果 MCP 无法在单条线上分段设置边界条件**，则采用替代方案：在几何阶段将每个环带创建为独立的线段（共 10 段），然后对偶数段单独施加 Sound Hard Boundary。\n\n#### 4.4 对称轴条件\n- r=0 的边界（对称轴）自动设为 **Axial Symmetry**（轴对称条件）\n- COMSOL 在 2D Axisymmetric 模式下会默认处理，无需手动设置\n\n#### 4.5 PML 设置\n- 为上、下、右外侧的三个 PML 子域分别添加 **PML** 节点\n- PML 类型：Spherical 或 Cartesian（对平面波使用 Cartesian）\n- 典型 PML 厚度：5-10 个网格单元，20 mm 足够\n\n#### 4.6 波带片外侧区域（r > ρ_10 到 r = R_domain）\n- 此区域 z=0 处没有波带片结构，声波自由通过\n- 不需要额外设置\n\n---\n\n### 第五步：网格与求解\n\n#### 5.1 构建网格\n- 使用 **用户控制网格 (User-controlled mesh)**\n- 最大单元大小：lam/6 ≈ 1.4 mm（每个波长至少 6 个单元，确保精度）\n- 最小单元大小：0.2 mm（波带片边缘附近加密）\n- 在波带片边界（z=0）附近添加 **边界层网格 (Boundary Layer)** 或局部加密\n- 在 PML 域中使用扫掠网格或映射网格（沿吸收方向 5-8 层）\n- 执行\"构建所有 (Build All)\"\n\n#### 5.2 创建研究\n- 添加 **频域 (Frequency Domain)** 研究\n- 频率列表：f0 (40 kHz)\n- 如果需要扫频（可选）：设置频率范围 30 kHz ~ 50 kHz，步长 2 kHz，观察不同频率下的聚焦效果\n\n#### 5.3 运行计算\n- 点击 Compute\n- 如果计算报错（内存不足、不收敛等），请读取错误日志并尝试：\n  - 放大网格单元尺寸\n  - 减小仿真域尺寸\n  - 检查 PML 设置\n  - 确认材料参数无遗漏\n\n---\n\n### 第六步：结果提取与后处理\n\n求解完成后，进行以下后处理：\n\n#### 6.1 二维声压分布（伪彩色图）\n- 创建 **2D Plot Group**\n- 添加 **Surface** 绘图\n- 表达式：`acpr.p_t`（总声压）或 `20*log10(abs(acpr.p_t)/1[Pa])`（dB 尺度）\n- 关注区域：z ∈ [40, 200] mm, r ∈ [0, 60] mm（焦点附近）\n- 保存此图为 \"声场分布热图.png\"\n\n#### 6.2 轴向声压曲线（验证焦距）\n- 创建 **1D Plot Group**\n- 添加 **Line Graph**\n- 线段位置：r=0（对称轴），z ∈ [40, 200] mm\n- 表达式：`abs(acpr.p_t)` 或 `20*log10(abs(acpr.p_t))`\n- 从曲线中找到声压最大值对应的 z 坐标 → 这就是实测焦距 z_max\n- **关键：比较 z_max 与设计焦距 F_design (120 mm)，计算偏差 ΔF = |z_max - 120|/120 × 100%**\n\n#### 6.3 焦平面径向声压曲线（提取 FWHM）\n- 创建 **1D Plot Group**\n- 添加 **Line Graph**\n- 线段位置：z = z_max（实测焦距），r ∈ [0, 60] mm\n- 表达式：`abs(acpr.p_t)`\n- 从曲线中找到峰值声压 p_max，然后找 p = p_max * 0.707 的两个 r 位置\n- **FWHM_r = 2 × |r_half - 0|**（因为是轴对称，半宽即半高全宽的一半）\n- 记录值：FWHM_r 应 ≤ 20 mm（设计目标）\n\n#### 6.4 焦点增益计算\n- 在同一 z 位置（z_max），分别读取有波带片和无波带片时的声压：\n  - U_max = 有波带片时焦点处声压\n  - U_0 = 无波带片时同位置声压（需要再跑一次无波带片的对照仿真，或从入射波幅值推算）\n- **Gain = 20 × log10(U_max / U_0)**\n- 记录值：增益应 ≥ 10 dB（设计目标）\n\n#### 6.5 亚像素焦点精确定位\n- 导出焦点邻域（z ∈ [z_max-15, z_max+15] mm, r ∈ [0, 30] mm）的声压数据\n- 导出为 CSV 或文本文件，格式：`r, z, p_abs`\n- 此数据用于后续 Python 二维高斯拟合，提取亚像素精度焦点坐标\n\n#### 6.6 导出报告用图\n- 保存以下图像用于竞赛报告：\n  1. 二维声场分布伪彩色图（标注焦点位置）\n  2. 轴向声压曲线（标注理论焦距和实测焦距）\n  3. 焦平面径向声压曲线（标注 FWHM）\n  4. 有无波带片对比曲线（标注增益）\n\n---\n\n### 第七步：变参扫描（可选，时间允许时执行）\n\n#### 7.1 环数对比\n- 修改 N_rings 参数或重新建模，分别仿真 N=5, 15, 20 的波带片\n- 比较不同环数的焦点增益和 FWHM\n\n#### 7.2 频率对比\n- 在频域研究中设置扫频范围 30~50 kHz，步长 2 kHz\n- 提取各频率下的焦点增益，分析频率偏移对聚焦效果的影响\n\n#### 7.3 材料缺陷模拟\n- 将某个遮挡环改为开放（模拟 3D 打印缺陷）\n- 或将某个开放环改为遮挡\n- 观察缺陷对聚焦效果的影响，为实验误差分析提供依据\n\n---\n\n### 关键检查点（每步完成后确认）\n\n- [ ] 参数表定义完成，环半径计算值与理论值吻合\n- [ ] 几何构建成功，波带片边界各分段 ID 已记录\n- [ ] Air 材料已分配\n- [ ] 压力声学物理场配置完成，背景平面波方向正确（+z）\n- [ ] Sound Hard Boundary 正确施加在偶数环上\n- [ ] PML 设置正确\n- [ ] 网格构建成功，波带片附近有足够分辨率\n- [ ] 频域求解收敛\n- [ ] 二维声压热图显示焦点位于 120 mm 附近\n- [ ] 轴向曲线能提取明确的峰值位置\n- [ ] 增益、FWHM 指标满足设计要求\n\n---\n\n如果任何步骤遇到 MCP 接口报错，请：\n1. 先确认上一步是否完全执行成功\n2. 用坐标查询替代 ID 盲猜\n3. 如遇 MCP 不支持的操作（如分段边界条件），采用替代方案（独立线段或薄实体域）\n4. 读取 COMSOL 的 Build Log / Solver Log 获取具体错误信息\n```\n\n---\n\n## 二、配套 Python 后处理脚本（仿真数据高斯拟合）\n\nCOMSOL 导出 CSV 数据后，用以下脚本进行亚像素焦点定位：\n\n```python\n\"\"\"从 COMSOL 仿真数据中提取亚像素焦点坐标\"\"\"\nimport numpy as np\nfrom scipy.optimize import curve_fit\nimport pandas as pd\n\n# 读取 COMSOL 导出的数据（格式：r, z, p_abs）\n# data = pd.read_csv(\"comsol_focal_region.csv\")\n\ndef gaussian_2d(X, A, r0, z0, sigma_r, sigma_z, B):\n    \"\"\"二维高斯模型\"\"\"\n    r, z = X\n    return A * np.exp(-((r - r0)**2 / (2*sigma_r**2) + (z - z0)**2 / (2*sigma_z**2))) + B\n\n# 准备数据（r, z 网格和对应的声压值 p）\n# r_grid, z_grid = np.meshgrid(r_unique, z_unique)\n# p_values = data['p_abs'].values.reshape(len(z_unique), len(r_unique))\n\n# 初始猜测\n# p0_guess = [p_max, 0, 120, 5, 15, p_bg]  # A, r0, z0, sigma_r, sigma_z, B\n\n# 拟合\n# popt, pcov = curve_fit(gaussian_2d, (r_grid.ravel(), z_grid.ravel()),\n#                        p_values.ravel(), p0=p0_guess)\n\n# r0_fit, z0_fit = popt[1], popt[2]\n# FWHM_r = 2.355 * popt[3]\n# FWHM_z = 2.355 * popt[4]\n# print(f\"焦点坐标: r={r0_fit:.2f} mm, z={z0_fit:.2f} mm\")\n# print(f\"焦距偏差: {abs(z0_fit - 120)/120*100:.1f}%\")\n# print(f\"焦斑 FWHM_r = {FWHM_r:.2f} mm, FWHM_z = {FWHM_z:.2f} mm\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## 三、仿真预期结果与报告用途\n\n| 输出项 | 预期值 | 报告中的位置 |\n|--------|--------|-------------|\n| 焦点 z 坐标 | 120 ± 5 mm | 实验原理验证 |\n| 焦点增益 | ≥ 10 dB | 性能指标表 |\n| FWHM_r | ≤ 20 mm | 焦斑尺寸 |\n| FWHM_z | ≤ 40 mm | 轴向焦深 |\n| 声场热图 | 焦点处红色高亮 | 报告配图 |\n\n---\n\n## 四、后续工作衔接\n\n仿真完成后，将 COMSOL 结果与实验实测对比：\n1. 焦距偏差归因于加工误差（环半径偏差）+ 温度影响（声速修正）\n2. 增益偏差归因于换能器指向性 + 环境反射\n3. FWHM 偏差归因于机械扫描步长限制 vs 仿真连续采样\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1904,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":38016,"output_tokens":7833,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"1c37d203-b7f1-42f1-8024-a00d376c9fb2","timestamp":"2026-05-29T08:38:15.613Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"d:\\豆包\\vscode文件","sessionId":"2563aa1c-2760-4099-ae80-555560773076","version":"2.1.145","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"claude-code-comsol-comsol-multiphysics-groovy-otter"}
