{"type":"file-history-snapshot","messageId":"242e4f37-9592-48e7-b2db-6a4789248001","snapshot":{"messageId":"242e4f37-9592-48e7-b2db-6a4789248001","trackedFileBackups":{"D:\\钉钉\\学习工作文件\\物理实验创新竞赛\\超声菲涅尔波带片_完整项目执行方案_终版.txt":{"backupFileName":"47cac596a445be75@v2","version":2,"backupTime":"2026-05-31T03:23:20.320Z"},"C:\\Users\\Nijika\\.claude\\plans\\claude-code-comsol-comsol-multiphysics-groovy-otter.md":{"backupFileName":"55f0495606e8e9b1@v5","version":5,"backupTime":"2026-05-30T00:45:42.597Z"},"D:\\钉钉\\学习工作文件\\物理实验创新竞赛\\超声菲涅尔波带片_实验仿真方案与审查报告.txt":{"backupFileName":"eddc95bc00476e1f@v3","version":3,"backupTime":"2026-05-30T00:45:42.597Z"}},"timestamp":"2026-05-31T04:08:24.588Z"},"isSnapshotUpdate":false}
{"parentUuid":"242e4f37-9592-48e7-b2db-6a4789248001","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"cbc17e9d-31ab-4c72-9ce0-0ff2b0640b67","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about all the resistors needed for the project. Let me think through all the circuits and list every resistor required:\n\n1. **发射链路 (MOSFET gate)**:\n   - 100Ω gate resistor (current limiting) - 1x\n   - 10kΩ pull-down resistor (防止浮空) - 1x\n\n2. **AD620 增益设置**:\n   - Rg = 500Ω for G=100 - 1x\n   - Formula: Rg = 49.4kΩ/(G-1), G=100 → Rg ≈ 499Ω ≈ 500Ω\n\n3. **TL072 有源精密整流电路**:\n   - Need to think about the full-wave precision rectifier circuit\n   - This requires several resistors to set gains\n   - For the second stage amplifier (Channel A): need feedback resistors\n   - For the precision rectifier (Channel B): need feedback resistors\n   - Typical values depend on the circuit topology\n\n4. **DS18B20 上拉电阻**:\n   - 4.7kΩ pull-up on DQ pin - 1x\n\n5. **ADS1115 I2C 上拉电阻**:\n   - Usually built into the module, but if not: 4.7kΩ on SDA and SCL - 2x (but typically these are on the ADS1115 module already)\n\n6. **Arduino to A4988**:\n   - No special resistors needed, direct GPIO connection\n\nLet me think about the TL072 precision rectifier circuit more carefully:\n\n**Channel A: Second stage amplifier (non-inverting, gain ~5-10)**\n- Need: Rf (feedback) and Rg (gain) resistors\n- For non-inverting: Gain = 1 + Rf/Rg\n- If Gain=10: Rf=10kΩ, Rg=1kΩ (or Rf=100kΩ, Rg=10kΩ)\n\n**Channel B: Precision full-wave rectifier**\nThis is a more complex circuit. A typical design uses:\n- Two op-amp stages for full-wave rectification\n- But since we only have one op-amp channel left (channel B), we might use a simpler half-wave precision rectifier or a different topology\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The TL072 has 2 channels. Let me think about a practical circuit:\n\nOption 1: Half-wave precision rectifier (simpler, uses 1 op-amp channel)\n- Input resistor, feedback resistor, 2 diodes in feedback loop\n- Only needs channel B\n\nOption 2: Full-wave precision rectifier (better, needs 2 op-amp channels typically)\n- Would need both channels A and B for the rectifier part\n- But channel A is supposed to be the second stage amplifier\n\nActually, there's a classic precision full-wave rectifier that uses 2 op-amps. But if channel A is already used for second-stage amplification, then only channel B is left for rectification.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The signal chain is:\nTCT40-16R → AD620(G=100) → TL072_CH_A(second stage amp, G=5-10) → TL072_CH_B(precision rectifier) → ADS1115\n\nSo Channel B needs to do the rectification. A half-wave precision rectifier with 1 op-amp is simpler:\n\nHalf-wave precision rectifier:\n- Input resistor Rin (e.g., 10kΩ)\n- Feedback resistor Rf (e.g., 10kΩ, for unity gain)\n- 2 diodes in the feedback loop (1N5819)\n\nFor the second stage amplifier (Channel A, non-inverting):\n- Rf and Rg to set gain\n- For G=6: Rf=10kΩ, Rg=2kΩ or similar\n\nAnd I also need to think about the full-wave version. A common single-op-amp full-wave rectifier doesn't really exist without additional diodes in the input. Let me stick with a practical approach:\n\n**Precision half-wave rectifier + RC filter for envelope detection:**\n\nActually wait, the user said they want \"精密有源整流\" - this is for precision detection of the 40kHz signal envelope. Let me think about what's most practical:\n\nFor the rectifier stage, a precision half-wave rectifier using 1 op-amp channel:\n- Rin = 10kΩ\n- Rf = 10kΩ  \n- 2x 1N5819 in feedback loop\n- Output goes through RC low-pass filter to extract envelope\n\nFor the second stage amplifier:\n- Non-inverting amplifier, G=5-10\n- Need 2 resistors (Rf and Rg per op-amp)\n\nSo total resistors needed:\n\n1. 100Ω - MOSFET gate current limiting (1x)\n2. 10kΩ - MOSFET gate pull-down (1x) \n3. 500Ω - AD620 Rg for G=100 (1x) ← This is critical\n4. 4.7kΩ - DS18B20 pull-up (1x)\n5. For TL072 Channel A (non-inverting amp, G=~6):\n   - Rf = 10kΩ (1x)\n   - Rg = 2kΩ (1x) → gives G = 1 + 10/2 = 6\n   (or Rf=47kΩ, Rg=10kΩ for G≈5.7)\n6. For TL072 Channel B (precision half-wave rectifier):\n   - Rin = 10kΩ (1x)\n   - Rf = 10kΩ (1x) → unity gain\n7. Optional: RC filter for envelope - but this uses capacitor, not resistor? Actually it might have a load resistor.\n\nWait, I should also think about whether ADS1115 module already has I2C pull-ups. Most ADS1115 modules have built-in 4.7kΩ pull-ups on SDA/SCL. If the module doesn't have them, you'd need 2x 4.7kΩ resistors. But most Chinese modules do include them.\n\nLet me also reconsider the precision rectifier circuit. Actually for the TL072 channel B doing a precision rectifier:\n\nA standard half-wave precision rectifier (super diode) circuit:\n- One resistor Rin between input and inverting input\n- Two diodes in feedback (one to output, one to ground typically)\n- One feedback resistor Rf\n\nActually for the simplest precision rectifier (half-wave):\n- Rin = 10kΩ (input resistor)\n- Diode D1: cathode to op-amp output, anode to junction  \n- Diode D2: anode to junction, cathode to output node\n- Rf = 10kΩ (feedback)\n- R_load = 10kΩ (output to ground, with capacitor for envelope)\n\nActually the standard \"super diode\" precision rectifier is:\n- Non-inverting input = signal\n- Output goes through diode (anode at op-amp output)\n- Feedback from cathode back to inverting input\n- This eliminates Vf\n\nWait, let me think about this more carefully. For our application, we're rectifying a 40 kHz AC signal to get its envelope. A precision half-wave rectifier followed by a low-pass filter would work.\n\nLet me simplify and just give practical numbers:\n\nFor the TL072 circuits, typical resistor values would be in the 1kΩ-100kΩ range. The exact values depend on the specific circuit topology. Let me recommend a reasonable set of resistors:\n\nCommon values needed across the whole project:\n- 100Ω (1x) - gate resistor\n- 500Ω (1x) - AD620 Rg (or use 470Ω + 30Ω in series, or just a 510Ω which gives G≈98, close enough)\n- 2kΩ (1x) - TL072 gain setting\n- 4.7kΩ (1x) - DS18B20 pull-up\n- 10kΩ (4-5x) - gate pull-down, TL072 precision rectifier circuit\n- 47kΩ (1x) or 100kΩ (1x) - TL072 feedback alternatives\n\nActually, 500Ω is not a standard resistor value. Common E12 values are: 470Ω, 510Ω, 560Ω.\n\nFor AD620 Rg=500Ω:\n- Closest standard: 510Ω → G = 1 + 49400/510 ≈ 97.9 (close enough to 100)\n- Or 470Ω → G = 1 + 49400/470 ≈ 106\n- Or use two 1kΩ in parallel = 500Ω exactly\n\nLet me compile a practical BOM. I'll recommend buying a small assortment kit since individual resistors cost almost nothing and having extras is useful.\n\nActually, let me just be direct and practical. The student bought 100x 100Ω resistors which is only one value. They definitely need more values. Let me list exactly what's needed and suggest the cheapest approach.","signature":"cbc17e9d-31ab-4c72-9ce0-0ff2b0640b67"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":715,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":149248,"output_tokens":2984,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"bfec8cdd-b1d2-4eaa-8d09-8707698863d9","timestamp":"2026-05-31T04:09:06.824Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"d:\\豆包\\vscode文件","sessionId":"2563aa1c-2760-4099-ae80-555560773076","version":"2.1.145","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"claude-code-comsol-comsol-multiphysics-groovy-otter"}
{"parentUuid":"bfec8cdd-b1d2-4eaa-8d09-8707698863d9","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"cbc17e9d-31ab-4c72-9ce0-0ff2b0640b67","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"text","text":"100 只 100Ω 只解决了 MOSFET 栅极电阻这一个地方，确实差远了。我把全部电阻需求理一遍：\n\n---\n\n### 项目中所有电阻需求\n\n| 序号 | 阻值 | 数量 | 用在哪里 | 说明 |\n|------|------|------|----------|------|\n| 1 | **100Ω** | 1 | MOSFET 栅极限流 | 已有 |\n| 2 | **10kΩ** | 5 | 栅极下拉 + TL072 电路 | 见下方电路图 |\n| 3 | **500Ω** | 1 | AD620 增益设定 Rg | G=100，关键精度 |\n| 4 | **4.7kΩ** | 1 | DS18B20 DQ 上拉 | OneWire 必需 |\n| 5 | **1kΩ** | 2 | TL072 通道A 增益 | 设 G≈6 |\n| 6 | **47kΩ** | 1 | TL072 通道A 反馈 | 与 1kΩ 配出 G≈6 |\n\n实际只要 **5 种阻值**：100Ω、500Ω、1kΩ、4.7kΩ、10kΩ、47kΩ。\n\n---\n\n### 每个电阻的电路位置\n\n**发射链路（2 颗）**：\n```\nArduino D5 ── 100Ω ──┬── Gate\n                      │\n                     10kΩ\n                      │\n                     GND\n```\n\n**AD620 增益（1 颗）**：\n```\nAD620 引脚 1 ── 500Ω ── AD620 引脚 8\n                    ↑\n              Rg=500Ω → G=1+49.4k/0.5k≈100\n              \n注：500Ω 不是标准值，买 510Ω 也行（G≈98，差别可以忽略）\n    或者用两颗 1kΩ 并联=500Ω 精确\n```\n\n**TL072 通道A — 第二级放大（2 颗）**：\n```\n                     ┌─ 47kΩ ─┐\n                     │         │\n输入 ──┬── TL072(+)  │  ┌──┤(-)├── 输出\n       │             │  │\n       └── 1kΩ ──────┴──┤\n                         │\n                        GND\n\n增益 = 1 + 47/1 ≈ 48（太大了，改一下...）\n```\n\n等一下，TL072 第二级只需要 5-10 倍。用 **10kΩ + 2.2kΩ** 更合适：\n- 增益 = 1 + 10/2.2 ≈ 5.5 倍\n- 或者干脆用一个 **10kΩ 电位器**（可调增益，调试方便）\n\n**TL072 通道B — 有源精密半波整流（3 颗）**：\n```\n输入 ── 10kΩ ──┬── TL072(-)\n                │\n               10kΩ ──┬── D1(1N5819) ──┬── 输出\n                │     │                │\n                └─────┤               10kΩ\n                      │                │\n                      ├── D2(1N5819) ──┤\n                      │                │\n                    TL072(+) ── GND   GND\n```\n用 3 颗 10kΩ。\n\n**DS18B20（1 颗）**：\n```\nDS18B20 DQ ──┬── Arduino D6\n              │\n             4.7kΩ\n              │\n             +5V\n```\n\n---\n\n### 汇总\n\n| 阻值 | 用量 | 可买 |\n|------|------|------|\n| 100Ω | 1 | 已有 |\n| 510Ω（≈500Ω）| 1 | 买 10 只，¥0.5 |\n| 1kΩ | 0（暂不需要）| — |\n| 2.2kΩ | 1 | 买 10 只，¥0.5 |\n| 4.7kΩ | 1 | 买 10 只，¥0.5 |\n| 10kΩ | 5 | 买 20 只，¥1 |\n| 10kΩ 电位器 | 1 | ¥1-2 |\n\n---\n\n### 最省事的方案\n\n让同学直接买一盒 **1/4W 金属膜电阻混装包**（淘宝搜\"电阻包 1/4W 常用 30 种\"），¥10-15 一盒，里面 100Ω 到 1MΩ 各几十颗，常用值全有。再单独加一颗 **10kΩ 3296 电位器**（¥1-2）用于 TL072 增益微调。\n\n比零买还便宜，以后调电路也不缺电阻。"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":715,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":149248,"output_tokens":2984,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"98bfd1fe-5d4b-4873-b381-cb8cf87d22d1","timestamp":"2026-05-31T04:09:25.939Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"d:\\豆包\\vscode文件","sessionId":"2563aa1c-2760-4099-ae80-555560773076","version":"2.1.145","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"claude-code-comsol-comsol-multiphysics-groovy-otter"}
