{"parentUuid":"c1996fd8-cffa-4acf-a39b-2778e85162c8","isSidechain":false,"message":{"id":"09dd1969-07fa-4204-9f4d-df044e7a4cc3","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"deepseek-v4-pro","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user has all their parts and needs me to guide them through the physical assembly process step by step. They need a detailed, practical guide on how to build the entire system. Let me think about what they need:\n\n1. The mechanical assembly (scanning platform)\n2. The electronic circuits (emission, reception, control)\n3. How to connect everything together\n4. What the final setup should look like\n5. Testing procedures\n\nI should create a comprehensive assembly guide. Since this is a hands-on task, I should be very practical and clear. Let me write this as a detailed document and save it to their project folder.\n\nLet me think about the structure:\n1. Tools needed (already have)\n2. Step 1: Mechanical assembly (motor + T8 screw + bracket)\n3. Step 2: Emission circuit (Arduino + MOSFET + transducer)\n4. Step 3: Reception circuit (AD620 + TL072 + ADS1115)\n5. Step 4: Motor driver circuit (A4988)\n6. Step 5: Limit switches\n7. Step 6: Temperature sensor\n8. Step 7: Everything together - final wiring diagram\n9. Step 8: Power-up and testing sequence\n\nI should write this as a practical guide, not a specification document. The user needs to know exactly what wire goes where, in what order to assemble things, and how to verify each step.","signature":"09dd1969-07fa-4204-9f4d-df044e7a4cc3"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":151772,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":4747,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"stop_details":null},"type":"assistant","uuid":"2c7069ac-9732-40a5-a